  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the treatment of a cancerous disease of the
      peritoneum with complete cytoreductive surgery with intraperitoneal chemohyperthermia using
      oxaliplatin plus irinotecan.

      This is a Phase II study with 100 patients. Origins of the tumors: these include colon,
      rectum, appendix, peritoneum, and endocrine tumors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
